ecessary bedrock of analysis that will prove vital for anyone with a stake in this important debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSocial securityzUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh  asocial security, reform, retirement, aging, labor, workforce, savings, pension, ira, poverty, government, politics, nonfiction, economics, policy, bankruptcy, insolvency, mortality, fertility, marriage, divorce, women, gender, immigration, nominal earnings, paul ryan, benefit offset, gw bush, estate tax, revenue, demsim, diamond-orszag, taxation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022630033740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226300368423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226300368/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles